1.body: Two main reasons; Worlds' official servers are old, slowly deteriorating, and probably unmaintained . Worlds is old . The shutdown of the servers is inevitable. TLDR: To keep Worlds' legacy going for future generations.

10.body: For BUDDYLISTUPDATE, I ended up in the NET.worlds.network.BuddyListUpdateCmd class. Here, I can review the methods which this class contains, and I notice that one happens to have the name send. I can now reference the raw packet data from a network proxy like Wireshark with this method and connect the dots.

8.body: A Java decompiler. I think Java Decompiler is a neat one. Setting the netdebug flag within your worlds.ini file to 255.
8.title: Prerequisites

9.body: Run Worlds, login, walk around, just gather some sample data. Open your Gamma.log file within a text editor. Open Java Decompiler and drag your worlds.jar onto it; opening it. Within your Gamma.log, find a network request, e.g [18803] test.3dcd.com:6650: send(BUDDYLISTUPDATE fuwn 1). Note the command used, e.g. BUDDYLUSTUPDATE. Within Java Decompiler, bring up the Search feature using Ctrl+Shift+S and tick all the search options. Profit.
